Velut uno ictu. The commentatore illustrate the force of this expression by reference to Caligula's wish (Vid. Seu. de ira. 3, 19), that the Roman people had but one neck, ut seelera sua in unum ictum et unum diem cogeret.

Albanam arcem. A favorite retreat of Dom. (situated at the foot of the Alban Mount, about seventeen miles from Rome), where he sometimes convened the Senate, and held his court with its trqop of informers, cf. note, 43: cursores.
